msg: Merged revisions r1196212 r1196223 from tomcat/trunk:
Implement self-guard against unexpected call to parseHeaders() after the parsing has already been completed
without a prior call to recycle() or nextRequest().
One such occurrence was caused by a bug that did not recycle the buffer and was fixed a while ago.

AbstractHttp11Processor handling of ISE from parseHeaders() is to reject the request with response status 400 and close the socket. The message is visible only when debug logging is enabled in AbstractHttp11Processor.
